tip.icon: Icons used to configure pages, which will be displayed in menus and tabs. Usually used with icon libraries, if it is an http link, the image will be loaded automatically.
tip.path: Used to configure the access path in the address bar.
tip.permission: Used to configure the permissions of a page or button. Only users with the corresponding permissions can access the page. If no configuration is made, no permissions are required.
tip.component: Component or path to configure the page.
tip.componentName: Used to configure the name of the page corresponding to the component path, often used in conjunction with page caching. It is required to be unique.
tip.title: Used to configure the page title, which will be displayed in menus and tabs. Generally used with internationalization. Priority is higher than the menu name.
tip.activePath: Used to configure the currently activated menu. Sometimes the page is not displayed in the menu and it is used when the parent menu needs to be activated.
tip.keepAlive: Used to configure whether to enable caching for a page. If enabled, the page will be cached and will not be reloaded. This is only valid when the tab is enabled.
tip.hideInMenu: Used to configure whether the page is hidden in the menu. If hidden, the page will not be displayed in the menu.
tip.hideInTab: Used to configure whether the page is hidden in the tab. If hidden, the page will not be displayed in the tab.
tip.hideInBreadcrumb: Used to configure whether the page is hidden in the breadcrumbs. If hidden, the page will not be displayed in the breadcrumbs.
tip.hideChildrenInMenu: It is used to configure whether the sub-pages of a page are hidden in the menu. If hidden, the sub-pages will not be displayed in the menu.
tip.badgeType: The type of logo to use for the configuration page.
tip.badge: The logo used for the configuration page, which will be shown in the menu.
tip.badgeVariants: Used to configure the logo color of the page. The optional values are default, destructive, primary, success, danger, warning. You can also customize the color.
tip.affixTab: Used to configure whether the page is fixed as a tab. Once fixed, the page cannot be closed.
tip.affixTabOrder: Used to configure the sorting of fixed tabs on the page, in ascending order.
tip.iframeSrc: Used to configure the iframe address of the embedded page. After setting, the corresponding page will be embedded in the current page.
tip.link: Used to configure the external link jump path, which will open in a new window.
tip.menuVisibleWithForbidden: The configuration page can be seen in the menu, but the access will be redirected to 403.
